claim.claim-text:
7. A method of operating a non-volatile memory, comprising:
programming first content including user data into a first data storage area;
verifying that the first content is correctly programmed in the first data storage area;
subsequently programming second content including user data into a second data storage area; and
concurrently with said programming second content, writing to the second data storage area an indication that the first data storage area is correctly programmed.
